column5: Fishindevil made his way up to Haliburton. I worked nights the night before so had to sleep in a little, then later met him up the road at the lake, and jumped in his boat.  sunrise    what a great outfit to fish out of, super comfy, lots of top end for hitting different spots    now for some fish pics, Fishindevil put on a clinic out there!,    spinnerbaits were a steady producer (even without a blade!)    Fishindevil with a nice fall bass    I even got in on the action too    sunset    back at the cottage, just in time for a rib dinner, perfect!    I went looking for a different species the next evening    thanks Fishindevil, a great day, great weather (sunburn in October!), hopefully we can hook up again
Gotta love the fall smallies......great pics
hey, you're new around here, how about a little introduction?
glad to have you out anytime chris !!!! we will fish again for sure !!! very nice walleye you got too !!! cheers man....
Good stuff guys! Those are some nice bass, but the walleye looks delicious  S.
Cool, looks like you two had a good time, with some fish and good eats.  I love it up there this time of year!!

Not surprisingly, there dont seem to be any other boats in the picture.  Best time of year for bronzebacks for sure! Good fishing and ribs waiting for you after? Priceless. Looks like a great day, thanks for sharing.
Nice little meet-up. Looked like a great fall day out there too
Good to see you boys hooked up and put some nice bass in the boat !!
